<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-05-07T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-05-07T18:00:00-05:00" n="623" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d623">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">367N.1115/218: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Consul at Jerusalem</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Steger</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-05-07T19:00:00-04:00">May 7, 1941—7
                                    p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Your 63, 1st. It is anticipated that such vessels as may be sent to
                                the Red Sea will not be suitable or available for the transportation
                                of passengers.</p>
                            <p>Suggest you keep in touch with Legation Cairo concerning availability
                                transportation facilities for returning Americans.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>